 Here is one way to insert NBT by string on _setstack in Java:

```java
// Import NBT classes
import net.minecraft.nbt.CompoundTag;
import net.minecraft.nbt.JsonToNBT;

// NBT string 
String nbtString = "{display:{Name:'{\"text\":\"My Item\"}'}}";

// Parse NBT 
CompoundTag nbt = JsonToNBT.parseTag(nbtString);

// Set NBT on stack
_setstack.setTag(nbt);
```

The key steps are:

1. Import NBT classes from net.minecraft.nbt
2. Create a String containing the NBT data in JSON format
3. Use JsonToNBT to parse the String into a CompoundTag 
4. Call setTag() on the ItemStack to apply the NBT

Let me know if you need any clarification or have additional questions!

 You're right, my previous code example won't work since JsonToNBT doesn't exist in the version of Minecraft Forge you are using. 

Here is an updated way to insert NBT by string on an ItemStack using the NBT classes available in Forge:

```java
// Import NBT classes
import net.minecraft.nbt.CompoundTag; 
import net.minecraft.nbt.StringTag;

// NBT string
String nbtString = "{display:{Name:'{\"text\":\"My Item\"}'}}";

// Parse NBT
CompoundTag nbt = new CompoundTag();
nbt.putString("display", StringTag.valueOf(nbtString));

// Set NBT on stack 
_setstack.setTag(nbt);
```

The key differences are:

- Use CompoundTag and StringTag instead of JsonToNBT
- Manually create a CompoundTag
- Add the NBT string as a StringTag value

Let me know if this updated approach works or if you have any other questions!

 Here is how you can insert that specific NBT data as a string on an ItemStack:

```java
// NBT string
String nbtString = "{Damage:0,Enchantments:[{id:\"minecraft:sharpness\",lvl:3s},{id:\"minecraft:unbreaking\",lvl:3s}],display:{Lore:['{\"italic\":false,\"text\":\"Lore text\"}','{\"italic\":false,\"text\":\"Lore text 2\"}']}}";

// Create NBT tag
CompoundTag nbt = new CompoundTag();

// Add NBT string 
nbt.putString("tag", StringTag.valueOf(nbtString)); 

// Set NBT on stack
_setstack.setTag(nbt);
```

The key points:

- I put the full NBT data into a string, escaping quotes and using single quotes for the JSON lore strings
- Create a new CompoundTag 
- Add the NBT string under a "tag" key using StringTag.valueOf()
- Apply the CompoundTag to the ItemStack

This will insert that complex NBT structure into the ItemStack as a string. Let me know if you have any other questions!

