 The issue is that you are putting the entire NBT string under a blank key "", when it needs to be under a proper key like "tag".

Try this:

```java
String nbtString = "{Damage:0,Enchantments:[{id:\"minecraft:sharpness\",lvl:3s},{id:\"minecraft:unbreaking\",lvl:3s}],display:{Lore:['{\"italic\":false,\"text\":\"Lore text\"}','{\"italic\":false,\"text\":\"Lore text 2\"}']}}";

// Create NBT tag
CompoundTag compoundTag = new CompoundTag();

// Add NBT string under "tag" key  
compoundTag.putString("tag", nbtString);  

_setstack = Items.DIAMOND_SHOVEL.getDefaultInstance();
_setstack.setTag(compoundTag);

ItemHandlerHelper.giveItemToPlayer(_player, _setstack);
```

The key points:

- Put the NBT string under a proper key "tag" in the CompoundTag
- Apply that CompoundTag to the ItemStack

This should properly insert the NBT data. Let me know if you still have any issues!
